gomodel:SYNGO_960  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors overexpressed GFP-tagged CK2b in the presynaptic neuron of the fly NMJ. GFP signal was observed in presynaptic terminals, overlapping with vGlut signals. This suggests that CK2b is localized to the presynapse.. Experimental description: Generation of CK2a and CK2b constructs and transgenes\nThe ORFs of CK2a and CK2b were amplified by PCR from the cDNA plasmids LD27706 and RE31047 (Drosophila Genomic Research Center)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
